> Errr...let's talk...Haven't thought about concave pistons in awhile, so
> is the deck height really measured at the center of the piston or on the
> edges???

Yes, it's measured at the edge of the piston, not the center, which is
dished.  I assumed the flat bar you mentioned would have the hole in it for
the plunger of the gauge more or less at its middle, which would be fine for
non-TypeIV engines but presents a problem for the TypeIV.

